WEBVTT

00:00.484 --> 00:01.664
Here come the fireworks!

00:01.730 --> 00:03.246
<i>Previously, on</i>
"SWAT"...

00:03.808 --> 00:05.285
She hate him deep.

00:05.373 --> 00:06.410
She's got her reasons, D.

00:06.498 --> 00:08.426
You ditched Mom, Wendy and me,
and you never came back!

00:08.513 --> 00:09.775
I didn't do right by you.

00:09.863 --> 00:11.681
You might want to think
about mending fences

00:11.769 --> 00:12.911
and owning up
to your mistakes.

00:12.998 --> 00:15.392
And I'm talking about
really owning up to them.

00:15.480 --> 00:17.004
To Mom.

00:24.592 --> 00:25.785
Street's brother.

00:25.910 --> 00:27.024
Foster brother.

00:27.111 --> 00:28.832
- Nate Warren.
- The reason I'm here

00:28.920 --> 00:30.175
is I need your help.

00:30.263 --> 00:31.558
You owe me one.

00:34.180 --> 00:35.886
I had to hit four places

00:36.167 --> 00:38.183
just to find
Mama Joan's favorites.

00:38.905 --> 00:41.212
- Yeah.
- Thanks for coming.

00:41.644 --> 00:42.996
This means a lot.

00:44.100 --> 00:46.379
It means a lot
having you back in my life.

00:46.496 --> 00:47.629
Paying respects
to the woman

00:47.717 --> 00:49.394
who brought us together
only seems right.

00:49.482 --> 00:51.574
The best foster mom
I've ever had.

00:52.671 --> 00:54.972
She'd be so proud of you,
Streeter.

00:55.535 --> 00:57.293
LAPD...

00:57.446 --> 00:58.675
SWAT.

00:59.855 --> 01:00.928
Who
would've thought?

01:01.015 --> 01:02.574
She'd be proud of you, too,
man.

01:02.877 --> 01:04.452
Steady job,
paying your bills.

01:04.540 --> 01:05.613
You're killing it.

01:05.802 --> 01:07.918
Nah, the truth is

01:08.006 --> 01:10.019
work ain't so good
these days.

01:11.315 --> 01:12.765
I'm in some trouble, man.

01:13.215 --> 01:15.144
Last week,
after I closed the bar,

01:15.232 --> 01:16.621
two guys bust in.

01:16.845 --> 01:18.717
Ski masks and guns.

01:18.805 --> 01:21.019
We've been robbed before,
but this was different.

01:21.107 --> 01:22.309
And they weren't
looking for cash.

01:22.396 --> 01:23.527
What were they
looking for?

01:23.615 --> 01:24.616
Heroin.

01:24.979 --> 01:26.113
My boss, Nolan?

01:26.201 --> 01:28.035
He's into some
shady business.

01:28.123 --> 01:29.191
And I guess he uses

01:29.279 --> 01:30.754
the bar for a stash house.

01:30.910 --> 01:32.568
Somehow the guys
knew about it,

01:32.655 --> 01:34.020
and grabbed the drugs
from the back room.

01:34.107 --> 01:36.048
So your boss gets ripped off,
why is that your problem?

01:36.135 --> 01:38.386
Because he blames me
for the lost product.

01:38.500 --> 01:39.644
50 grand.

01:39.732 --> 01:41.734
He says I must've been in
on the job.

01:41.898 --> 01:43.456
- Were you in on it?
- What?!

01:43.544 --> 01:45.082
- No!
- I'm sorry.

01:45.271 --> 01:47.761
Listen, I still got some
cop buddies in Long Beach.

01:47.849 --> 01:49.498
I'll make some calls.
With you as a witness,

01:49.585 --> 01:51.065
- we'll put this Nolan guy away.
- No!

01:51.152 --> 01:53.504
Hell no! Look,
Nolan's connected.

01:53.677 --> 01:55.837
You'll find me in a gutter
before he's even arraigned.

01:55.925 --> 01:57.114
Well, then, what
do you want me to do?

01:57.201 --> 01:58.300
I don't know.

01:58.823 --> 02:00.215
Maybe you should talk to him.

02:00.303 --> 02:02.433
Tell him you know all
about his operation,

02:02.556 --> 02:04.925
and you'll turn a blind
eye if he lets me walk.

02:05.013 --> 02:07.527
Do you have any idea
how illegal that is?

02:08.401 --> 02:11.564
Do you remember the blood oath
that we had as kids, man?

02:12.011 --> 02:14.066
I'm in some serious
trouble, brother.

02:14.203 --> 02:17.636
So, please...
can you help me?

02:20.614 --> 02:21.716
I was too selfish

02:21.804 --> 02:23.793
to deserve you
and the family we had made.

02:23.881 --> 02:25.855
Did you practice
saying all this?

02:25.943 --> 02:28.636
Yes, I did, and a whole lot
of other ways to apologize.

02:28.723 --> 02:30.386
For running off
with some other woman?

02:30.474 --> 02:31.490
For leaving me

02:31.578 --> 02:32.925
and our children behind?

02:33.013 --> 02:35.597
You all deserved so
much better from me.

02:36.307 --> 02:37.331
I'm sorry.

02:37.419 --> 02:38.471
You're sorry?!

02:38.559 --> 02:39.605
You're sorry now?

02:39.693 --> 02:41.529
Why makes you think
I believe you now?

02:41.617 --> 02:43.269
I'm not asking you
to forgive me.

02:43.663 --> 02:45.879
I can't go back
and fix the past.

02:45.967 --> 02:47.668
I'm just
asking you to see...

02:47.756 --> 02:48.777
Daniel, stop!

02:48.865 --> 02:50.207
- Daniel, stop!
- Mom, Pop!

02:50.295 --> 02:52.465
Pop, that's enough,
Pop!

02:53.766 --> 02:55.395
It's all right, baby.

02:55.483 --> 02:56.582
It's okay.

02:56.670 --> 02:58.324
I was just getting
ready to leave.

02:58.777 --> 03:01.066
I left your food
on the stove.

03:01.201 --> 03:02.507
Mama, what's going on?

03:02.595 --> 03:05.316
Baby, I'm really okay.

