03:14.074 --> 03:15.722
Okay, real talk...
Why was my mama crying?

03:15.810 --> 03:18.728
You asked me
to mend fences.

03:18.816 --> 03:20.681
- Your words!
- I told you to mend fences,

03:20.769 --> 03:23.363
- not upset her!
- Life is complicated, son.

03:24.168 --> 03:26.488
Well, let me make it
real simple for you.

03:26.742 --> 03:28.121
I ain't about to let you break

03:28.209 --> 03:29.863
my mother's heart
all over again.

03:30.221 --> 03:32.056
Am I ever gonna
be able to do

03:32.144 --> 03:33.840
anything right in your eyes?

03:37.579 --> 03:38.925
Never mind.

03:43.402 --> 03:44.567
Did you get her to sleep?

03:44.655 --> 03:46.457
Yeah, finally.

03:47.201 --> 03:49.230
She's having
the same nightmares again.

03:54.132 --> 03:55.386
All right, I'll, uh,

03:55.516 --> 03:57.300
I'll talk
to her teacher tomorrow.

03:57.403 --> 03:59.152
See if there's something
going on at school.

03:59.240 --> 04:00.730
Oh, come on, David.

04:00.818 --> 04:02.472
We both know
it's not the school.

04:03.879 --> 04:05.254
I'm not blaming you,
I just...

04:05.342 --> 04:06.605
ever since our house
got shot up...

04:06.692 --> 04:08.105
What are we
supposed to do?

04:09.819 --> 04:12.519
I booked a session
tomorrow with Dr. Collins.

04:12.952 --> 04:14.258
For all of us.

04:14.784 --> 04:17.065
I know you don't like
the idea of therapy,

04:17.154 --> 04:19.180
but our kids need
to talk through this.

04:19.608 --> 04:21.430
And we need
to be there for them.

04:24.072 --> 04:25.220
All right.

04:26.125 --> 04:27.306
I'm on call tomorrow,

04:27.394 --> 04:28.970
but hopefully
it'll quiet, so...

04:30.269 --> 04:31.357
Hey.

04:31.470 --> 04:32.830
Huh?

04:34.617 --> 04:35.923
We'll get
through this.

04:50.940 --> 04:52.674
- El Monte?
- Yes.

04:53.932 --> 04:54.969
"Taifa."

04:55.065 --> 04:56.518
That a Somali name?

04:56.852 --> 04:57.953
Yes, sir.

04:58.041 --> 04:59.600
Oh, righteous.
My, uh,

04:59.688 --> 05:01.221
my wife's
from Somalia.

05:01.353 --> 05:02.500
Charge your phone?

05:02.588 --> 05:03.866
Yeah, thanks.

05:04.307 --> 05:06.031
Yeah, she, um,
she was born there,

05:06.119 --> 05:07.522
but she left
when she was a baby.

05:07.609 --> 05:08.929
Civil war and all that.

05:09.017 --> 05:10.361
Her parents
say it was brutal.

05:10.503 --> 05:12.515
We all have
different lives now.

05:12.736 --> 05:14.494
Amen to that.

05:15.432 --> 05:17.259
Have we crossed paths
at a barbeque or something?

05:17.346 --> 05:19.010
I feel like I've seen your face.

05:19.142 --> 05:20.404
I doubt it.

05:20.655 --> 05:22.266
I don't get out much.

05:33.408 --> 05:34.547
Uh, you know what?

05:34.635 --> 05:36.242
Change of plans.
You can, uh,

05:36.330 --> 05:38.446
you can actually just
let me out right here.

05:38.534 --> 05:40.401
Get some bad news
on your phone?

05:40.489 --> 05:42.031
Yeah, just a text.

05:42.119 --> 05:44.221
But, seriously,
anywhere here is good.

05:46.098 --> 05:47.588
Hey, what're you doing?
Stop.

05:47.922 --> 05:49.097
Stop.

06:24.425 --> 06:26.969
Looking at a barricade situation
in a corner deli.

06:27.057 --> 06:29.233
Two men, one of 'em armed,
holding the other hostage.

06:29.321 --> 06:31.111
Let's get 'em both out alive.

06:34.268 --> 06:36.695
Man, Luca makes driving this
thing look easier than it is.

06:36.807 --> 06:38.169
Yeah, well,
Black Betty's a load.

06:38.257 --> 06:39.329
You put a dent in her, Tan,

06:39.416 --> 06:41.302
- Luca's gonna have your ass.
- Yeah, yeah.

06:41.390 --> 06:42.618
What's the latest
with Luca, anyway?

06:42.705 --> 06:44.461
Anything new from
his doctors?

06:45.562 --> 06:47.274
Street! You with us?

06:47.361 --> 06:50.304
Yeah, sorry.
He's basically going stir crazy,

06:50.392 --> 06:52.157
but the doctor says he's got
to stay off the hip

06:52.244 --> 06:54.053
for a few more weeks while
they try this new therapy.

06:54.140 --> 06:55.381
We'll get him back
to beast mode.

06:55.468 --> 06:56.665
But for today,
we're one man down,

06:56.752 --> 06:58.164
so stay sharp.

07:00.895 --> 07:02.742
Hey. What's going on?

07:02.859 --> 07:05.328
I'm just thinking
about some family stuff.

07:19.039 --> 07:20.586
This is the LAPD!

07:20.674 --> 07:22.539
Come out
with your hands up!

07:29.493 --> 07:31.070
Drop the gun!
Do it now!

07:31.158 --> 07:32.571
No, no, no, no. It's okay.
I'm the good guy.

07:32.658 --> 07:34.791
I said drop the gun now!
I got a shot, boss.

07:34.907 --> 07:36.309
- He's a crazy man!
- This guy's a monster!

07:36.396 --> 07:37.530
What are you waiting for?
Shoot him!

07:37.617 --> 07:38.336
He's the one you want!

07:38.424 --> 07:40.234
Drop the gun or we will shoot!

07:43.644 --> 07:44.993
O-Okay.

07:46.640 --> 07:48.029
All right.

07:48.367 --> 07:49.859
Move! Move!

07:51.179 --> 07:52.959
Hands behind your head.
Behind your head.

07:53.047 --> 07:54.193
This is 20-David to command.

07:54.281 --> 07:56.271
Code 4.
Suspects in custody.

07:56.359 --> 07:58.599
He's crazy. He attacked
me in my own car.

07:58.687 --> 08:01.435
You pulled the gun.
It's his. Th-This is Aden Syed.

08:01.522 --> 08:04.312
Aden Syed, okay?
He's a monster.

08:08.437 --> 08:10.851
We're gonna take you both in
and sort this out.

08:21.262 --> 08:22.568
Photo's pretty old.

08:22.803 --> 08:24.461
Could be the guy
we brought in.

08:24.819 --> 08:26.086
I don't know, maybe.

08:26.174 --> 08:28.562
A lot more than maybe.
Fingerprints came back.

08:28.664 --> 08:30.246
That warlord on the screen?

08:30.333 --> 08:32.804
Same man sitting
in holding, Aden Syed.

08:32.892 --> 08:34.289
There's an Interpol
Red Notice out on him.

08:34.376 --> 08:35.990
Red Notice?
Issued by who?

08:36.078 --> 08:37.265
International Criminal Court.

08:37.352 --> 08:38.794
- This guy's wanted by the Hague?
- Mm-hmm.

08:38.881 --> 08:40.299
So he's pretty
straight-up evil.

08:40.405 --> 08:42.365
Hondo, you served in
Somalia back then.

08:42.453 --> 08:44.434
- What do you know about him?
- Syed was responsible

08:44.521 --> 08:46.685
for murdering thousands
during the civil war,

08:46.773 --> 08:48.547
and enslaving
children as soldiers.

08:48.656 --> 08:49.918
They called him
the "Saw Man"

08:50.005 --> 08:51.615
for the way
he would cut body parts off

08:51.702 --> 08:53.132
anyone who resisted him.

09:01.390 --> 09:02.680
Oh, you've been gone
for a minute.

09:02.767 --> 09:04.031
Thought maybe we'd seen
the last of you.

09:04.118 --> 09:05.523
Oh, sorry to disappoint.

09:05.611 --> 09:07.734
I was working a special project
for the mayor.

09:07.929 --> 09:11.125
This is Fabrice Vachel from the
International Criminal Court.

09:11.254 --> 09:13.976
And Agents Lufkin and Sampath.

09:14.377 --> 09:16.414
ICC's been going after Syed
for a while.

09:16.590 --> 09:19.947
We almost had Syed 25 years ago,
but he slipped away in Somalia.

09:20.035 --> 09:21.882
We're not taking
any chances this time.

09:21.970 --> 09:24.865
They'll be assuming custody of
Mr. Syed until his extradition.

09:24.953 --> 09:26.788
Well, happy to get him off
our hands, trust me.

09:26.875 --> 09:28.625
The news is already out
about his arrest,

09:28.713 --> 09:30.454
so sooner's better
for both of us.

09:41.854 --> 09:44.570
You ever cross paths with Syed
when you were in Somalia?

09:45.664 --> 09:47.320
Not face-to-face.

09:47.976 --> 09:50.007
But I saw plenty
of his handiwork.

10:08.043 --> 10:10.123
- What the hell was that?
- Shots. We're taking fire.

10:10.723 --> 10:12.870
This is Agent Lufkin. Mayday!
We're taking fire out here!

10:12.957 --> 10:14.942
Back up, back up, back up!

10:19.012 --> 10:20.208
Get to the gate!

10:20.342 --> 10:21.864
Cover left!

